==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Disfellowship
<hw>Dis*fel"low*ship</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Fellowship</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <def>To exclude from
fellowship; to refuse intercourse with, as an associate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An attempt to <qex>disfellowship</qex> an evil, but to fellowship
the evildoer.</q> <rj><qau>Freewill Bapt. Quart.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disfiguration</ent>⟦br⟧
